    19Рєњ
    20Рєњ**mdBook** is a command line tool to create books with Markdown.
    21РєњIt is ideal for creating product or API documentation, tutorials, course materials or anything that requires a clean,
    22Рєњeasily navigable and customizable presentation.
    23Рєњ
    24Рєњ* Lightweight [Markdown] syntax helps you focus more on your content
    25Рєњ* Integrated [search] support
    26Рєњ* Color [syntax highlighting] for code blocks for many different languages
    27Рєњ* [Theme] files allow customizing the formatting of the output
    28Рєњ* [Preprocessors] can provide extensions for custom syntax and modifying content
    29Рєњ* [Backends] can render the output to multiple formats
    30Рєњ* Written in [Rust] for speed, safety, and simplicity
    31Рєњ* Automated testing of [Rust code samples]
    32Рєњ
    33РєњThis guide is an example of what mdBook produces.
    34РєњmdBook is used by the Rust programming language project, and [The Rust Programming Language][trpl] book is another fine example of mdBook in action.
    35Рєњ
    36Рєњ[Markdown]: format/markdown.md
    37Рєњ[search]: guide/reading.md#search
    38Рєњ[syntax highlighting]: format/theme/syntax-highlighting.md
    39Рєњ[theme]: format/theme/index.html
    40Рєњ[preprocessors]: format/configuration/preprocessors.md
