cli/test.md
     1Рєњ# The test command
     3РєњWhen writing a book, you sometimes need to automate some tests. For example,
     4Рєњ[The Rust Programming Book](https://doc.rust-lang.org/stable/book/) uses a lot
     5Рєњof code examples that could get outdated. Therefore it is very important for
     6Рєњthem to be able to automatically test these code examples.
     7Рєњ
     8РєњmdBook supports a `test` command that will run all available tests in a book. At
     9Рєњthe moment, only Rust tests are supported.
