cli/watch.md
     1Рєњ# The watch command
     3РєњThe `watch` command is useful when you want your book to be rendered on every
     4Рєњfile change. You could repeatedly issue `mdbook build` every time a file is
     5Рєњchanged. But using `mdbook watch` once will watch your files and will trigger a
     6Рєњbuild automatically whenever you modify a file; this includes re-creating
     7Рєњdeleted files still mentioned in `SUMMARY.md`!
     8Рєњ
