format/mathjax.md
     1Рєњ# MathJax support
     3РєњmdBook has optional support for math equations through
     4Рєњ[MathJax](https://www.mathjax.org/).
     5Рєњ
     6РєњTo enable MathJax, you need to add the `mathjax-support` key to your `book.toml`
     7Рєњunder the `output.html` section.
     8Рєњ
     9Рєњ```toml
    10Рєњ[output.html]
    11Рєњmathjax-support = true
    12Рєњ```
    13Рєњ
    14Рєњ>**Note:** The usual delimiters MathJax uses are not yet supported. You can't
    15Рєњcurrently use `$$ ... $$` as delimiters and the `\[ ... \]` delimiters need an
    16Рєњextra backslash to work. Hopefully this limitation will be lifted soon.
    17Рєњ
    18Рєњ>**Note:** When you use double backslashes in MathJax blocks (for example in
    19Рєњ> commands such as `\begin{cases} \frac 1 2 \\ \frac 3 4 \end{cases}`) you need
    20Рєњ> to add _two extra_ backslashes (e.g., `\begin{cases} \frac 1 2 \\\\ \frac 3 4
    21Рєњ> \end{cases}`).
    22Рєњ
    23Рєњ
    24Рєњ### Inline equations Рђд
    32Рєњ### Block equations Рђд

