format/summary.md
     1Рєњ# SUMMARY.md
     3РєњThe summary file is used by mdBook to know what chapters to include, in what
     4Рєњorder they should appear, what their hierarchy is and where the source files
     5Рєњare. Without this file, there is no book.
     6Рєњ
     7РєњThis markdown file must be named `SUMMARY.md`. Its formatting
     8Рєњis very strict and must follow the structure outlined below to allow for easy
     9Рєњparsing. Any element not specified below, be it formatting or textual, is likely
    10Рєњto be ignored at best, or may cause an error when attempting to build the book.
    11Рєњ
    12Рєњ### Structure Рђд
    93Рєњ### Example Рђд

format/theme/README.md
     1Рєњ# Theme
     3РєњThe default renderer uses a [handlebars](https://handlebarsjs.com) template to
     4Рєњrender your markdown files and comes with a default theme included in the mdBook
     5Рєњbinary.
     6Рєњ
     7РєњThe theme is totally customizable, you can selectively replace every file from
     8Рєњthe theme by your own by adding a `theme` directory next to `src` folder in your
     9Рєњproject root. Create a new file with the name of the file you want to override
    10Рєњand now that file will be used instead of the default file.
    11Рєњ
    12РєњHere are the files you can override:
    13Рєњ
    14Рєњ- **_index.hbs_** is the handlebars template.
    15Рєњ- **_head.hbs_** is appended to the HTML `<head>` section.
    16Рєњ- **_header.hbs_** content is appended on top of every book page.
    17Рєњ- **_css/_** contains the CSS files for styling the book.
    18Рєњ    - **_css/chrome.css_** is for UI elements.
    19Рєњ    - **_css/general.css_** is the base styles.
    20Рєњ    - **_css/print.css_** is the style for printer output.
    21Рєњ    - **_css/variables.css_** contains variables used in other CSS files.
    22Рєњ- **_book.js_** is mostly used to add client side functionality, like hiding /
    23Рєњ  un-hiding the sidebar, changing the theme, ...
    24Рєњ- **_highlight.js_** is the JavaScript that is used to highlight code snippets,
    25Рєњ  you should not need to modify this.
    26Рєњ- **_highlight.css_** is the theme used for the code highlighting.
    27Рєњ- **_favicon.svg_** and **_favicon.png_** the favicon that will be used. The SVG
    28Рєњ  version is used by [newer browsers].
    29Рєњ- **fonts/fonts.css** contains the definition of which fonts to load.
    30Рєњ  Custom fonts can be included in the `fonts` directory.
    31Рєњ
      РєњРђд

format/theme/editor.md
     1Рєњ# Editor
     3РєњIn addition to providing runnable code playgrounds, mdBook optionally allows them
     4Рєњto be editable. In order to enable editable code blocks, the following needs to
     5Рєњbe added to the ***book.toml***:
     6Рєњ
     7Рєњ```toml
     8Рєњ[output.html.playground]
     9Рєњeditable = true
    10Рєњ```
    11Рєњ
    12РєњAfter enabling editable code blocks, the `editable` attribute must be added to a
    13Рєњcode block to make it editable:
    14Рєњ
    15Рєњ~~~markdown
    16Рєњ```rust,editable
    17Рєњfn main() {
    18Рєњ    let number = 5;
    19Рєњ    print!("{}", number);
    20Рєњ}
    21Рєњ```
    22Рєњ~~~
    23Рєњ
    24РєњThe above will result in this editable playground:
    25Рєњ
    26Рєњ```rust,editable
    27Рєњfn main() {
    28Рєњ    let number = 5;
    29Рєњ    print!("{}", number);
    30Рєњ}
    31Рєњ```
    32Рєњ
      РєњРђд
    35Рєњ## Customizing the editor
    37РєњBy default, the editor is the [Ace](https://ace.c9.io/) editor, but, if desired,
    38Рєњthe functionality may be overridden by providing a different folder:
    39Рєњ
    40Рєњ```toml
    41Рєњ[output.html.playground]
      РєњРђд

format/theme/index-hbs.md
     1Рєњ# index.hbs
     3Рєњ`index.hbs` is the handlebars template that is used to render the book. The
     4Рєњmarkdown files are processed to html and then injected in that template.
     5Рєњ
     6РєњIf you want to change the layout or style of your book, chances are that you
     7Рєњwill have to modify this template a little bit. Here is what you need to know.
     8Рєњ
     9Рєњ## Data
    11РєњA lot of data is exposed to the handlebars template with the "context". In the
    12Рєњhandlebars template you can access this information by using
    13Рєњ
    14Рєњ```handlebars
    15Рєњ{{name_of_property}}
      РєњРђд
    41Рєњ## Handlebars helpers
    43РєњIn addition to the properties you can access, there are some handlebars helpers
    44Рєњat your disposal.
    45Рєњ
    46Рєњ### toc
    48РєњThe toc helper is used like this
    49Рєњ
    50Рєњ```handlebars
    51Рєњ{{#toc}}{{/toc}}
    52Рєњ```
      РєњРђд
    80Рєњ### resource
    82РєњThe path to a static file.
    83РєњIt implicitly includes `path_to_root`,
    84Рєњand accounts for files that are renamed with a hash in their filename.
    85Рєњ
    86Рєњ```handlebars
      РєњРђд
    90Рєњ### fa
    92РєњmdBook includes a copy of [Font Awesome Free's](https://fontawesome.com)
    93РєњMIT-licensed SVG files. It accepts three positional arguments:
    94Рєњ
    95Рєњ1. Type: one of "solid", "regular", and "brands" (light and duotone are not
    96Рєњ   currently supported)
      РєњРђд

format/theme/syntax-highlighting.md
     1Рєњ# Syntax highlighting
     3РєњmdBook uses [Highlight.js](https://highlightjs.org) with a custom theme
     4Рєњfor syntax highlighting.
     5Рєњ
     6РєњAutomatic language detection has been turned off, so you will probably want to
     7Рєњspecify the programming language you use like this:
     8Рєњ
     9Рєњ~~~markdown
    10Рєњ```rust
    11Рєњfn main() {
    12Рєњ    // Some code
    13Рєњ}
    14Рєњ```
    15Рєњ~~~
    16Рєњ
    17Рєњ## Supported languages
    19РєњThese languages are supported by default, but you can add more by supplying
    20Рєњyour own `highlight.js` file:
    21Рєњ
    22Рєњ- apache
    23Рєњ- armasm
      РєњРђд
    68Рєњ## Custom theme
    69РєњLike the rest of the theme, the files used for syntax highlighting can be
    70Рєњoverridden with your own.
    71Рєњ
    72Рєњ- ***highlight.js*** normally you shouldn't have to overwrite this file, unless
    73Рєњ  you want to use a more recent version.
      РєњРђд
    82Рєњ## Improve default theme
    84РєњIf you think the default theme doesn't look quite right for a specific language,
    85Рєњor could be improved, feel free to [submit a new
    86Рєњissue](https://github.com/rust-lang/mdBook/issues) explaining what you
    87Рєњhave in mind and I will take a look at it.
    88Рєњ
      РєњРђд

